result.execSummary:
The defendant Cody Ray Rehwinkel was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).
  • Ignition Interlock Device Tampering/Failure to Install, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 347.413(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.

Good Time Credit and Huber Privileges granted.   Defendant must complete ID process with the Waushara Co Sheriff's Department as to this case when reporting to serve the sentence.
Concurrent with: Waushara Co Case No. 2016CM000111
DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.

records.addlTxt: 16CM-111 and 16CM-143 with 16TR-949 - All Cases Called @ 4:20 PM: Defendant Cody Ray Rehwinkel in court with attorney David W. Keck.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Global resolution recited by DA with expected argued terms on SEH.  Def and counsel concur with State's recital.  16CM-111:   Second Amended Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and potential punishment.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.   Defendant advised of potential punishment.  Agrees with 1 prior conviction as recited by the Court. Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  16CM-111 Plea Ct 1 (OWI 2):   NC  16CM-143 Plea Cts 1 (OAR 2) and 2 (FTI IID): NC  Court accepts pleas and enters JOC.  Ct 2 outright dismissal and Ct Nos 3 and 4 DRI of 16CM-111.  16TR-949 also DRI.  Argument by DA.  Argument by Atty Keck.  Statement by Def:  None offered.  The Court:  16CM-111 - 18 mos probation.  Conditions:  5 days WCJ, Huber, GT and No TS credit; AODA and any follow thru;   The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars with the exception of the R Bar in Plainfield while working and maintaining Ab Sobriety while working, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. 12 mos DL Rev/IID for 12 mos.  $1429.00 fine plus $42.50 Blood Draw Fee with Ct Appt Atty Fees.  Any bond to be applied to Atty Fees first - 60 DTP any Bal with PP.  16CM-143:  Cts 1 and 2 - 45 days WCJ as to each count - concurrent to one another and concurrent with 16CM-111 5 day SEH - Report:  12/1/2016 - GT and No TS credit; Court costs as to each count - 60 DTP or PP.   DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice.  Appeal Rights given.  Def must report to DOC by the end of the day tomorrow due the late hour today.  Court advises Def to obtain Occ DL as soon as able due to the IID requirement.  Atty Billing to be provided by week's end.
